## Round 9 addendum: object type annotations removed
Review comment on otel_export's calls list ('Why is this object? Don't use
this type here or anywhere else in this stack'). Fixes:
- otel_export: calls was list[dict[str, object]] holding
  {'mode': ..., 'req': ...} dicts that CallCreateBatchReq validated later.
  Now constructs the real models directly:
  list[tsi.CallBatchStartMode | tsi.CallBatchEndMode] — typed at the
  source, no validation-time coercion.
- _OrderableOrNone.__eq__(self, other: object) deleted entirely: the class
  is only ever a list.sort key and timsort invokes only __lt__, so __eq__
  was dead code (its removal also retired the PLW1641 noqa). The object
  annotation there was the typeshed-required dunder signature, but the
  method itself was unnecessary.
- Swept the whole stack (module + every changed test file): zero
  object-typed annotations remain; the only 'object' occurrences left are
  JSON type-tag string literals and prose.

